header.gameNote: AMERICAS YOUTH CLASSIC AT EVANSVILLE IN

article.headline: Buffalo 77, Cleveland State 73
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Parnell Smith scored 24 points on 7-of-11 shooting to lead Buffalo past Cleveland State 77-73 Friday night in the America's Youth Classic. Smith also grabbed seven rebounds and shot 10-of-12 from the free throw line for the Bulls (2-1). Buffalo hit 26-of-54 field goal attempts (48 percent) and 19-of-27 free throws (70 percent). J'Nathan Bullock led Cleveland State (1-2) with 24 points on 9-of-15 shooting and seven rebounds. Joe Davis added 13 points and was 7-of-8 from the free throw line. Kevin Francis also grabbed seven rebounds for the Vikings, who led 35-28 at halftime but were unable to hold their lead. The Bulls outrebounded the Vikings 31-30. Both teams struggled from 3-point range as Cleveland State was 4-of-17 and Buffalo was 6-of-23.
